u-Kama Protocol

Coordinating Value Under Ecological Constraint

Whitepaper v1.0

Constraint at the core. Finance at the margin.

u-Kama is a system architecture for protecting and regenerating ecosystems by aligning economic coordination with ecological reality. Rather than asking nature to justify financial activity, the system requires economic participation to operate within the limits imposed by living landscapes.

Ecological truth within u-Kama emerges only when ecological processes persist through time and when independent witnesses confirm the condition of the land. Economic coordination occurs only after ecological continuity has been established.

The architecture therefore separates ecological reality from financial activity. Nature defines the constraint. Finance operates only at the boundary.

