Architectural Principles

The architecture follows three fundamental principles.

Ecological reality constrains economic activity.
Economic participation occurs only within the limits imposed by ecological continuity.

Financial systems remain separated from ecological truth.
Ecological memory cannot be priced, traded, or altered by financial activity.

Verification precedes coordination.
Economic coordination occurs only after ecological state has been independently verified.

Artificial intelligence may assist analytical processes within the system but does not function as a witness. A formal statement governing the use of AI within u-Kama is provided in Appendix H.

